locality: El Gualtal. Cresta del cerro Golondrinas Hembra. Bosque húmedo Montano Bajo. Vegetación arbustiva en la cresta de la montaña.

Cerro Golondrinas area, access via Chamorro property above El Carmen, which is above Hualchán. Flat hilltop before steep ridge crest approach to peak 2840. Stunted Upper Montane Forest, heavily festooned with moss.

Cerro Golandrinas. Primary forest and vegetation highly variable due to complex topography. Mossy, upper montane pluvial forest with trees up to 30 m tall in ravines and creek bottoms. Variously stunted forest and shrubbery on exposed slopes, ridges and peaks; some areas similar to paramo.
